HEADWORD: metate
<hw>me*ta"te</hw> <pr>(m⟦asl⟧*t⟦aum⟧"t⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp., fr. Mex. <ets>metlatl</ets>.]</ety> <def>A flat or somewhat
hollowed stone upon which grain or other food is ground, by means of a
smaller stone or pestle.</def> <mark>[Southwestern U. S. & Sp.
Amer.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

